Evans, Colorado Land Investment Project
About Evans, Colorado (USA)
The town of Evans is located 60 miles from Denver, the capital of Colorado. Evans has a growing economy fueled by large oil & gas companies, investors and agriculture. The technology, aerospace, construction, financial and health care sectors are also prominent in Evans with continued hiring and job opportunities. Job creation, strong population growth and a continued influx of new residents and businesses to the area have lead to an increased demand for housing in Evans.

The Project



Project Description
Evans, Colorado, USA
Area:   9,583,200 Sq ft (220 Acres)
Length:   6 years
Phases:   5
This 220 acre land investment opportunity arises in a context where the local economy is strong and growing. Local builders needs to bank lots in order to have inventory for the coming years.
There are many amenities located nearby the project including a school that is currently under construction immediately adjacent to this property. Include in this project acquisition are 1,168 shares of water in order to service more than 1,200 homes. Water shares are extremely valuable and rare, as only properties with water can be developed.
Offering a mix of products in order to reach all the market:
• Single family homes
• Townhomes
• Duplexes
• Triplexes
• Condos
• Parks
• Commercial and retail area

Colorado Population Growth

Source: U.S. Department of Commerce and Wells Fargo Securities, LLC, Dated Dec 30th, 2014
• Economic growth in Colorado has outpaced the nation for the past two years.
• Strong population growth and a relatively young population have fuelled job growth in the state.
• Colorado’s population is the third fastest growing of any state since 2010, rising a cumulative 6.1 percent.

Colorado’S Housing market

Source: U.S. Department of Commerce and Wells Fargo Securities, LLC, Dated Dec 30th, 2014
• Stronger population growth and improving household formations should drive home sales higher in the coming year and give single-family construction a much needed boost.
• Home prices have also rebounded well ahead of the nation and are now 12.4 percent above their pre-recession highs.

Focus Groups

ROI Land Investments, LTD. started the process, through focus groups, of validating the concept for the master plan in Evans Colorado project


